        </div>
        <div class="cover-meta-item">
          <span class="cover-meta-label">Active Pipeline</span>
          <span class="cover-meta-val" style="color:var(--gold-light);">$100,000,000</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cover-meta-item">
          <span class="cover-meta-label">Collateral</span>
          <span class="cover-meta-val">UCC-1 · 5 Independent Layers</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cover-divider"></div>

      <div class="cover-confidential">
        <div class="cover-confidential-title">⚠ Confidentiality &amp; Regulatory Notice</div>
        <p>This data room and all materials herein are strictly confidential and are provided solely for informational purposes to prospective accredited investors who have completed required verification. This document does not constitute an offer to sell, or a solicitation of an offer to buy, any securities. Any such offer will be made only through the Fund's Private Placement Memorandum prepared by SCALE LLP. Recipients may not reproduce, distribute, or disclose any portion without prior written consent of Draft Horse Capital Partners LLC. Forward-looking statements and target yields are not guarantees. All investment involves risk. Accredited investors only — Reg D 506(c).</p>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:28px;">
        <span class="tag tag-gold">Reg D 506(c)</span>
        <span class="tag tag-gold">§3(c)(1)</span>
        <span class="tag tag-blue">UCC-1 Five-Layer Lien</span>
        <span class="tag tag-green">Zero Fees</span>
        <span class="tag tag-green">Quarterly Income</span>
        <span class="tag tag-gold">Texas LLC · Est. February 2026</span>
        <span class="tag tag-blue">Gulfstream G550 Collateral</span>
        <span class="tag tag-gold">Sovereign &amp; Institutional Capital</span>
        <span class="tag tag-blue">Infrastructure Real Asset Layer</span>
        <span class="tag tag-gold">Section 892 Tax Analysis Recommended</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-page-notice">Draft Horse Capital Partners LLC — Confidential | For Informational Purposes Only | Not an Offer to Sell Securities</div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       02 — LETTER FROM THE CIO
  ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section" id="cio-letter">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-number">Section 02</div>
      <div class="section-title">Letter from the CIO</div>
      <div class="section-subtitle">A measured statement from Caleb Caraway on the credit philosophy, structural decisions, and alignment framework underlying Draft Horse Capital Partners</div>
      <div class="gold-rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="cio-letter">
      <div style="font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9.5px;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold-dim);margin-bottom:28px;">To Institutional Investors Evaluating Draft Horse Capital Partners</div>

      <p class="cio-letter-para">I will be direct about what this fund is, what it is not, and why I structured it the way I did. Draft Horse Capital Partners is a single-mandate secured private credit vehicle. It is not diversified across multiple borrowers or strategies. It does not deploy into an origination pipeline we are building after close. It is one credit facility — $100 million — extended to a single institutional PE sponsor against a five-layer collateral package that I designed specifically to minimize recovery exposure in the event that borrower cannot or will not perform. I am describing the fund this way at the outset because institutional allocators reviewing this document deserve precision, not a narrative that defers concentration risk to footnote disclosures.</p>

      <p class="cio-letter-para">The concentration is a deliberate underwriting decision, not a structural limitation. I know this borrower. I have evaluated their operations, their assets, and their incentives directly. I negotiated the lending terms, the covenant package, and the collateral architecture personally. I have equity exposure on both sides of this transaction — in the credit facility structure and in the aviation assets that serve as hard collateral. My capital is deployed alongside investor capital in the same position. I do not manage this fund from a distance, and I am not compensated by fees on committed capital. My economic interest derives entirely from the spread between what the PE sponsor pays the Fund and what the Fund pays investors. That structure means my incentive is to maximize deployment, maintain covenant compliance, and generate more spread — not to collect a management fee on capital sitting idle in a money market account.</p>

      <p class="cio-letter-para">The collateral architecture requires specific attention. Five independent layers — operating cash flows, physical real estate and inventory, portfolio company equity, Gulfstream G550 aviation assets under UCC-1 perfected first lien and FAA Civil Aviation Registry notation, and a PE sponsor guaranty from an entity with equity exposure on both sides of the transaction — were constructed because I am not willing to accept a lending structure where a single asset deterioration creates material principal exposure. Each layer is independently enforceable. Each has a distinct liquidity profile and a distinct legal enforcement pathway. In a default scenario, the Fund does not need all five layers to hold — it needs one. The recovery analysis under any stress case is materially superior to single-collateral structures, which remain the market standard in middle-market private credit.</p>

      <p class="cio-letter-para">On the exclusivity of the pipeline: this credit facility originated through a direct, bilateral relationship that predates the fund formation. It was not broker-sourced. It was not won through a competitive auction. The borrower is an institutional PE sponsor I know personally, who requires structured capital on terms that work for their operational planning horizon. The 36-month facility term serves both sides of the transaction — it provides the borrower with certainty for capital investment planning, and it provides the Fund with a matched-funding structure that eliminates redemption pressure and enables full deployment from day one. There is no ramp period. The deal is ready to execute upon initial close.</p>

      <p class="cio-letter-para">The 17% target yield at the top commitment tier is derived from the spread the borrower is willing to pay for a direct, collateral-backed relationship-sourced facility — not from a backward calculation that begins with what sounds attractive to investors. The yield is the product of the structure, not the other way around. I have zero management fee and zero carried interest in this fund because I believe the alignment between my interests and investor interests should be absolute: I earn only when the Fund earns above the fixed investor yield. If we underperform, I underperform. That is the only model I am willing to operate under. I present Draft Horse to qualified institutional allocators as a specific, documented, collateral-secured credit opportunity with a known borrower, a fully structured facility, and a quantifiable five-layer recovery framework. I am prepared to support every element of this presentation with documentation under appropriate confidentiality protocols.</p>

      <div class="cio-letter-sig">
        <div class="cio-letter-sig-name">Caleb Caraway</div>
        <div class="cio-letter-sig-title">CIO — Dark Horse Wealth Management &nbsp;|&nbsp; Managing Partner — Draft Horse Capital Partners LLC</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box">
      This letter represents the personal views of the Principal and is provided for informational context only. It does not modify, supersede, or supplement the Fund's Private Placement Memorandum. All investments involve risk. Target yields are not guaranteed. Prospective investors should review the complete PPM and consult their own advisors before investing.
    </div>
    <div class="section-page-notice">Draft Horse Capital Partners LLC — Confidential | For Informational Purposes Only | Not an Offer to Sell Securities</div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       03 — EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
  ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section" id="exec-summary">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-number">Section 03</div>
      <div class="section-title">Executive Summary</div>
      <div class="section-subtitle">Strategy, structure, yield, collateral, pipeline, and fee model — the complete overview</div>
      <div class="gold-rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="stat-grid">
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-value">17%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Maximum Target Yield (p.a.)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-value">$100M</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Active Deployment Pipeline</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-value">5</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Independent Collateral Layers</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-value">Zero</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Management Fees / Carry</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-value">Qtrly</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Distribution Frequency</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-box">
        <div class="stat-value">36 Mo.</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Investor Term / Matched Funding</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <div class="card card-gold">
        <h3>The Fund in One Paragraph</h3>
        <p>Draft Horse Capital Partners LLC is a single-mandate structured private credit fund that deploys capital through a direct, UCC-1 secured senior lending facility to a single institutional PE sponsor. The Fund is collateralized against five independent asset layers — operating cash flows, physical real estate and inventory, 100% portfolio company equity, Gulfstream G550 aviation assets, and a PE sponsor guaranty backed by dual equity alignment. Investors receive a target tiered yield of 9%–17% per annum — with the applicable tier rate fixed contractually at the time of subscription — paid quarterly, on a 36-month term with 100% principal return at maturity. Target yields are not guaranteed; distributions are contingent on Fund and borrower performance. The Fund charges zero management fees and zero carried interest. The borrower is already identified. The deployment is ready. The deal is waiting on investor capital, not the other way around.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Investment Strategy</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Single-mandate focus:</strong> One borrower relationship, one credit facility, maximum collateral depth and monitoring precision</li>
            <li><strong>Security perfected via UCC-1:</strong> First-priority claim against five independent collateral layers</li>
            <li><strong>Collateral-first underwriting:</strong> Every dollar lent is backed by specific, appraised, legally encumbered assets</li>
            <li><strong>36-month matched funding:</strong> Investor lock aligns perfectly with deployment term — no maturity mismatch, no redemption pressure</li>
            <li><strong>Zero-fee architecture:</strong> Fund retains spread above investor yield; GP incentive is to generate more, not charge more</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Structural Differentiators</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Dual-counterparty alignment:</strong> PE sponsor holds equity in both the borrowing entity AND the charter company — double incentive to prevent default</li>
            <li><strong>Aviation equity income:</strong> Fund holds 40% equity per Gulfstream G550 jet, targeting 24 jets — an independent income stream above and beyond the credit spread</li>
            <li><strong>Deployment-ready:</strong> No ramp period — first dollar in, first dollar deployed against an identified, documented facility</li>
            <li><strong>Institutional infrastructure:</strong> NAV Fund Services, Axos Bank, Spicer Jeffries LLP, SCALE LLP — operational standard of a mature institutional fund</li>
            <li><strong>Operator alignment:</strong> Principal deploys personal capital alongside investor capital — structural co-investment, not mere representation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>The Investor Value Proposition — Why This, Why Now</h3>
        <p>The fundamental question for any sophisticated allocator is not "what is the yield?" — it is "what am I actually buying?" In Draft Horse, you are buying a secured, senior position in a directly negotiated private credit facility, with a counterparty who is financially incentivized not to default on both the credit AND the hard asset collateral, on a 36-month term that matches deployment duration exactly, at a target yield whose tier rate is fixed at subscription and subject to no fee drag, originated by a principal who has been doing this professionally for years and who has his own capital in the same position.</p>
        <p>At the 17% tier — $50M+ committed — an investor receives $42,500 per quarter per $1 million invested, totaling $170,000 in annual income and $510,000 over the 3-year term, with $1,000,000 principal returned at maturity. Total value: $1,510,000 per $1 million committed. That is a 51% total return over 36 months, in a fully collateralized, no-fee, quarterly-income structure. For context, the S&amp;P 500 Total Return Index delivered approximately 29% over the 3-year period ending December 31, 2024 (source: Bloomberg), with daily mark-to-market volatility, no contractual income, and no collateral protection. Investors should evaluate this comparison in the context of the liquidity differential: Draft Horse requires a 36-month lock-up that public equities do not impose.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Principal Track Record:</strong> Caleb Caraway's flagship private credit vehicle, Corinthian Capital Partners, has delivered a documented 24% annual return to investors with distributions made monthly since inception. This track record is maintained at the operating entity level and is not audited by Spicer Jeffries LLP, which serves as auditor for Draft Horse Capital Partners specifically. Draft Horse is a separate, newly formed vehicle with its own independent audit and administration infrastructure. Prospective investors should not rely on Corinthian's track record as a guarantee of Draft Horse's performance.
      </div>

      <div style="background:rgba(8,12,24,0.7);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:5px;padding:28px 32px;margin-top:8px;">
        <div style="font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold);margin-bottom:14px;font-weight:700;">Institutional Due Diligence Framework — What Is Available and When</div>
        <p style="font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:16px;">The following materials are available to qualified institutional investors at the indicated stage of the evaluation process. All materials marked "NDA Required" are provided under mutual non-disclosure agreement executed prior to document transfer.</p>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Document / Information</th>
              <th>Availability</th>
              <th>Stage</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Private Placement Memorandum (PPM)</td>
              <td class="td-gold">Available — SCALE LLP</td>
              <td>Post-Accredited Investor Verification</td>
