      <!-- WHY 36 MONTHS -->
      <div class="card card-gold">
        <h3>Why 36 Months? — The Structural Case for the 3-Year Term</h3>
        <p>The 36-month investor commitment is a deliberate structural decision that creates alignment simultaneously across investors, the Fund, and the borrower. This is not a restriction — it is the mechanism that makes the yield achievable, and the discipline that protects every investor in the pool from the actions of every other.</p>
        <br>
        <div class="two-col">
          <div>
            <h4>What the 36-Month Term Does for Investors</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Rate locked at entry:</strong> Your tier rate is fixed at subscription and does not reset. In a declining rate environment, you continue earning at your locked rate. In a competitive landscape where yields compress, early investors are protected on the downside permanently.</li>
              <li><strong>Premium for commitment:</strong> The 9%–17% yield is explicitly priced to compensate for the liquidity premium. Shorter-duration capital cannot command this yield in any comparable instrument. The term is the source of the premium, not a cost of the premium.</li>
              <li><strong>No reinvestment risk:</strong> A defined 36-month term eliminates the compounding drag of redeploying capital at varying rates. Your return begins accruing from day one at a fixed, known rate.</li>
              <li><strong>Tax efficiency:</strong> A qualifying 36-month hold may receive long-term capital gains treatment on appreciation for eligible investors — reducing the effective tax burden relative to ordinary income treatment on shorter-duration instruments.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>What the 36-Month Term Does for the Fund and Borrower</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>No redemption pressure:</strong> The Fund cannot be forced to liquidate positions to meet redemptions. This enables full, immediate deployment without cash drag — every dollar earns from day one.</li>
              <li><strong>Matched funding architecture:</strong> The Fund deploys on 36-month tranches. Matching investor duration creates a perfect asset-liability match — eliminating the maturity mismatch that has caused structural failures in other private credit vehicles.</li>
              <li><strong>Stronger covenant negotiation:</strong> Stable committed capital enables the Fund to negotiate tighter covenants and better terms from borrowers. A fund vulnerable to redemption is a structurally weaker counterparty at the negotiating table.</li>
              <li><strong>Borrower operational certainty:</strong> A 36-month credit facility gives the PE sponsor certainty for long-term operational planning, capital investment, and growth — which is precisely why they're willing to pay the premium rate that generates the investor yield.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="callout" style="margin-top:16px;">
          <strong>Bottom Line:</strong> The 36-month term is the structural engine that makes 9%–17% yield achievable and sustainable. Investors are compensated, generously, for the stability their commitment provides. The lock-up is not a cost — it is the reason the yield exists.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
