  <section class="section" id="deployment">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-number">Section 08</div>
      <div class="section-title">$100M Deployment Model</div>
      <div class="section-subtitle">How investor capital flows, how the facility is structured, and exactly what investors receive — the complete economics</div>
      <div class="gold-rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <div class="card card-gold">
        <h3>Overview — The $100M Single-Mandate Deployment</h3>
        <p>Draft Horse's initial deployment is a single $100M structured credit facility extended to one institutional PE sponsor under a comprehensive credit agreement. The entire deployment occurs under the five-layer collateral architecture described in Section 07. From the moment investor capital closes, it is deployed — earning from day one, with no ramp period, no idle cash, and no speculative origination period.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:12px;">At the $50M+ AUM tier, investors receive the full 17% annual yield — the most attractive tier in the Fund's structure. This corresponds to quarterly distributions of 4.25% of invested principal, with 100% of principal returned at 36-month maturity. The Fund's economics above the 17% investor yield — the spread between what the borrower pays and what investors receive — remain with the Fund as the GP's compensation. This is why no fees are charged: the spread is the fee, and the incentive is to maximize it by ensuring full deployment and zero defaults.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- CAPITAL FLOW DIAGRAM -->
