      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Verdict — The Honest Assessment for a Sophisticated Allocator</h3>
        <div class="two-col">
          <div>
            <h4>Where Draft Horse Is Clearly Superior</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Net yield:</strong> 17% with zero fee drag versus 5–8% on public credit instruments after market pricing and, in BDC/PE cases, significant management fees and carry. This is not a marginal difference. It is a 2x–4x yield advantage.</li>
              <li><strong>Collateral depth:</strong> Five-layer UCC-1 perfected architecture versus the typical single lien — or, in BDC/HY cases, no lien at all. If a borrower defaults, the Fund has five independent recovery pathways. HY bondholders have an unsecured claim.</li>
              <li><strong>Fee structure:</strong> Zero management fee, zero carry, zero complexity. Every dollar of committed capital works for the investor. In a 1.5%/20% structure, the fee drag on a $10M position is $150K/year plus 20% of profits taken off the top. That is real money extracted from investor returns that Draft Horse simply does not charge.</li>
              <li><strong>No mark-to-market:</strong> Draft Horse's NAV does not fluctuate daily with rate moves or credit spread widening. An investment at 17% today is worth 17% tomorrow, regardless of what the Fed does. IG bondholders in 2022 lost 18% of NAV in a single year while earning 3% yield. That scenario is structurally impossible in Draft Horse.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>Where Alternatives Are Superior — The Honest Trade-Off</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Liquidity:</strong> Public market instruments offer daily liquidity. Draft Horse offers none. Investors who require the ability to exit within 36 months should not invest in Draft Horse. This is an explicit, unambiguous constraint and a material risk factor that should be fully understood before subscribing.</li>
              <li><strong>Diversification:</strong> Investment-grade bond portfolios or BDCs diversify across hundreds of issuers. Draft Horse is concentrated in a single borrower relationship. This concentration is the source of the yield premium — it is also a real risk that is disclosed fully in Section 11.</li>
              <li><strong>Track record:</strong> BlackRock, Ares, and Apollo have 10+ year fund track records. Draft Horse Capital Partners was formed in February 2026. The Principal's track record at Corinthian Capital Partners is compelling, but it is not the same as a 10-year institutional fund history. Investors should weight this appropriately.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="callout" style="margin-top:16px;">
          <strong>The Institutional Summary:</strong> For a qualified allocator with a 3-year time horizon who does not require interim liquidity and who can evaluate direct private credit on a collateral basis, Draft Horse offers a yield, fee structure, and collateral architecture that materially outperforms every comparable instrument in the market. The illiquidity trade-off is real and acknowledged. For the right investor with the right time horizon, it is also the reason the yield exists.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-page-notice">Draft Horse Capital Partners LLC — Confidential | For Informational Purposes Only | Not an Offer to Sell Securities</div>
  </section>

