      <div class="card" style="border:2px solid var(--gold);background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(201,168,76,0.06) 0%,rgba(8,12,24,0) 70%);">
        <h3>The Most Critical Operational Fact About Draft Horse</h3>
        <p>Draft Horse Capital Partners is not raising capital to search for a borrower. <strong>The borrower is already identified. The credit structure is fully developed. The collateral package is documented. The UCC-1 framework is ready to file upon close. There is zero ramp period.</strong> First dollar in — first dollar deployed, earning from day one.</p>
        <br>
        <p>This is the single most important operational differentiator between Draft Horse and virtually every other newly formed private credit fund in this market. Most first-time funds raise capital first and spend 12–24 months after close sourcing the deals they promised in their fundraising materials. During that period, investor capital sits in a money market account earning 4–5% while the manager collects the management fee and describes their deal pipeline as "active." Draft Horse has no pipeline to develop. It has a $100M commitment from an identified, diligenced, existing PE sponsor relationship that is ready to execute.</p>
        <div class="pipeline-bar" style="margin-top:20px;">
          <div class="pipeline-fill">$100,000,000 — Borrower Identified · Collateral Documented · Structure Ready · Deploying on Close</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Pipeline Characteristics</h3>
          <ul class="label-val-list">
            <li><span class="lv-label">Borrower Type</span><span class="lv-val">Institutional PE Sponsor (Confidential)</span></li>
            <li><span class="lv-label">Relationship Status</span><span class="lv-val">Existing — Direct Principal Relationship</span></li>
            <li><span class="lv-label">Pipeline Size</span><span class="lv-val td-gold">$100,000,000</span></li>
            <li><span class="lv-label">Facility Type</span><span class="lv-val">Senior Secured Credit Facility</span></li>
            <li><span class="lv-label">Deployment Term</span><span class="lv-val">36 Months per Tranche</span></li>
            <li><span class="lv-label">Collateral Type</span><span class="lv-val">Five-Layer (see Section 07)</span></li>
            <li><span class="lv-label">Deployment Timeline</span><span class="lv-val">Immediate Upon Fund Close</span></li>
            <li><span class="lv-label">Deal Source</span><span class="lv-val">Direct — No Broker or Intermediary</span></li>
            <li><span class="lv-label">Geographic Focus</span><span class="lv-val">United States (Texas Ecosystem)</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Why This Pipeline Is Different</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Not hypothetical — the borrower exists:</strong> The borrower is identified, diligenced, and has committed to terms. The pipeline is a documented commitment, not a projection.</li>
            <li><strong>No competitive process:</strong> This facility was not sourced through a broker, an investment bank, or an auction. It originated from a direct, private, years-long principal relationship. There is no competing bid, no spread compression from the deal-sourcing process, and no premium paid for access.</li>
            <li><strong>Collateral pre-assessed:</strong> The five-layer collateral package — cash flows, real assets, equity, aviation assets, PE sponsor guaranty — was assessed, documented, and structured before the capital raise began. Investors step into a structured facility, not an origination process.</li>
            <li><strong>Dual equity alignment in place:</strong> The PE sponsor's co-ownership of the charter company is a pre-existing structural fact — not something engineered for the fundraise. The alignment is real because the relationship predates the Fund.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Borrower Confidentiality &amp; Due Diligence Access</h3>
        <p>The identity of the PE sponsor is maintained in strict confidence at this stage of the capital raise. This is a contractual obligation between the Fund and the borrower — not a fundraising preference. The Fund recognizes that institutional and sovereign allocators conducting formal investment committee diligence require access to borrower identity, audited financials, and collateral documentation before proceeding to an allocation decision. That access is available and will be provided.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:12px;">Full borrower due diligence materials — including entity name and structure, portfolio company details, audited financial statements, independent collateral appraisals, aircraft registration documentation, and the redacted credit agreement — are available to qualified institutional investors subject to execution of a mutual non-disclosure agreement. SCALE LLP manages all disclosure and confidentiality protocols.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:12px;">Institutional and sovereign investors preparing a formal IC submission package should contact the Principal directly. The Fund is prepared to provide a structured, sequenced diligence process that accommodates formal institutional review timelines, including legal review by the investor's own outside counsel of the full offering document set. There is no accelerated subscription pressure — the Fund will support a thorough, documented due diligence process.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

      <div class="card" style="margin-top:8px;">
        <h3>Borrower Profile — Anonymous Summary</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:14px;">While the PE sponsor's identity remains confidential at this stage, the Fund can confirm the following factual characteristics of the borrower to assist institutional investors in preliminary due diligence assessment. Full disclosure is available under NDA.</p>

