  <section class="section" id="management">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-number">Section 12</div>
      <div class="section-title">Management</div>
      <div class="section-subtitle">Principal biography, track record, organizational structure, and platform overview</div>
      <div class="gold-rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <div class="card card-gold">
        <h3>Caleb Caraway — Principal &amp; Chief Investment Officer</h3>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:28px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <div style="flex:1;min-width:280px;">
            <p>Caleb Caraway is a multi-disciplinary investment principal and operator with a career spanning structured credit, private equity lending, fractional aviation, algorithmic trading, mineral resources, and institutional fine art. He serves as <strong>Managing Partner and CEO of Dark Horse Wealth Management</strong> — the private family office and governing entity at the top of his organizational structure — and as <strong>Senior Advisor at Aera Investment Bank</strong>, a full-service institutional advisory firm.</p>
            <br>
            <p>Caleb's private credit experience is the operational foundation underlying Draft Horse's structure. As Managing Partner of <strong>Corinthian Capital Partners</strong> — his flagship private credit vehicle — he has maintained a <strong>24% annual return to investors since inception, with distributions made monthly.</strong> This performance record is maintained at the operating entity level. Corinthian Capital Partners is a separate legal entity from Draft Horse Capital Partners and is audited by its own service providers. Past performance of Corinthian does not guarantee future results for Draft Horse. The relevance of the Corinthian track record is its evidence that the Principal has structured, managed, and distributed capital from a private credit vehicle through multiple market conditions — not that Draft Horse investors can extrapolate equivalent outcomes.</p>
            <br>
            <p>His personal balance sheet distinguishes him from typical fund managers in a meaningful way. Caleb operates as a multi-asset principal allocator with holdings spanning structured credit, private equity, aviation, precious metals, mineral resources, and fine art. His fine art holdings — appraised at over $541 million by Elena Kohn of Sotheby's — represent a long-duration capital allocation consistent with his investment philosophy of holding deeply held, appreciating assets over multi-year time horizons. Investors should note that the fine art portfolio is illiquid; the Principal's financial alignment with the Fund is reflected primarily through his co-investment of capital in the same position as investor capital (amount disclosed under NDA) and through his fee-free, spread-dependent compensation structure. He is not a fund manager who underwrites assets he has never owned. He is an operator who has personally managed, built, and held positions in the same asset categories that serve as Draft Horse's collateral.</p>
            <br>
            <p>Critically, Caleb deploys <strong>personal capital alongside investor capital</strong> in Draft Horse. This co-investment is structural, not rhetorical — his capital is subject to the same priority, the same collateral enforcement, and the same terms as investor capital. The specific co-investment amount is disclosed to investors under NDA at the subscription stage. When the Fund performs, Caleb performs alongside investors. When the Fund faces a workout scenario, Caleb's personal capital is in the same enforcement position as investor capital. There is no agency problem in Draft Horse because there is no separation between who manages the Fund and who bears the downside risk.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="min-width:220px;">
            <div class="card" style="margin:0;background:var(--navy-light);">
              <h4>Profile Highlights</h4>
              <ul class="label-val-list">
                <li><span class="lv-label">Role</span><span class="lv-val">Principal &amp; CIO</span></li>
                <li><span class="lv-label">Corinthian Track Record</span><span class="lv-val td-gold">24% p.a. — Monthly</span></li>
                <li><span class="lv-label">Personal Portfolio</span><span class="lv-val">$541M+ Fine Art (Sotheby's Verified)</span></li>
