  <!-- ============================================================
       14 — LEGAL & COMPLIANCE
  ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section" id="legal">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-number">Section 14</div>
      <div class="section-title">Legal &amp; Compliance</div>
      <div class="section-subtitle">Regulation D 506(c), §3(c)(1), accredited investor verification, Form D, and offering disclaimers</div>
      <div class="gold-rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Regulation D Rule 506(c)</h3>
          <p>Draft Horse Capital Partners offers its interests pursuant to <strong>Rule 506(c) of Regulation D</strong> under the Securities Act of 1933. Rule 506(c) permits issuers to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Engage in <strong>general solicitation and general advertising</strong> in connection with an offering</li>
            <li>Raise an <strong>unlimited amount of capital</strong> from an unlimited number of accredited investors</li>
            <li>Avoid SEC registration and associated ongoing reporting requirements</li>
          </ul>
          <br>
          <p>In exchange, Rule 506(c) requires the issuer to take <strong>reasonable steps to verify</strong> that all investors are, in fact, accredited. Self-certification alone is legally insufficient under 506(c).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>§3(c)(1) Fund Exclusion</h3>
          <p>The Fund relies on <strong>Section 3(c)(1) of the Investment Company Act of 1940</strong>, which excludes from the definition of "investment company" any issuer whose outstanding securities are beneficially owned by not more than <strong>100 persons</strong> and which is not making a public offering.</p>
          <br>
          <p><strong>Key implications:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Fund is not required to register as an investment company with the SEC</li>
            <li>Hard statutory limit of <strong>100 beneficial owners</strong></li>
            <li>No public offering permitted — consistent with Reg D private placement</li>
            <li>Fund must monitor investor count continuously against the statutory cap</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card card-gold">
        <h3>Accredited Investor Verification — Required Prior to Subscription</h3>
        <p>Unlike Rule 506(b) offerings, the Fund's 506(c) structure requires the Fund to take reasonable steps to verify accredited investor status before accepting any subscription. Accepted verification methods include:</p>
        <br>
        <div class="two-col" style="gap:14px;">
          <div>
            <h4>Individual Investor Pathways</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Net worth exceeding $1M (excluding primary residence), individually or jointly with spouse — verified by CPA, attorney, registered broker-dealer, or investment adviser</li>
              <li>Income exceeding $200K individually ($300K jointly) in each of the prior two years, with reasonable expectation of same in current year — verified by W-2, 1099, 1040, K-1, or confirmation letter</li>
              <li>FINRA Series 7, 65, or 82 license in good standing</li>
              <li>"Knowledgeable employee" of a registered investment fund</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>Entity Investor Pathways</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Total assets exceeding $5M (trusts, LLCs, corporations, partnerships)</li>
              <li>All equity owners are individually accredited investors</li>
              <li>Registered investment adviser, broker-dealer, or bank</li>
              <li>Family office with $5M+ AUM</li>
              <li>Family client of a family office meeting the above threshold</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #ef4444;">
        <h3 style="color:#f87171;">Offering Disclaimers — Required Reading</h3>
        <p style="font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;"><strong style="color:var(--white);">NOT AN OFFER TO SELL SECURITIES.</strong> This data room and all materials herein are provided for informational purposes only and do not constitute an offer to sell or solicitation to buy any securities. Any offer will be made only by means of a Private Placement Memorandum prepared by SCALE LLP to investors who have completed accredited investor verification.</p>
        <p style="font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;"><strong style="color:var(--white);">FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS.</strong> Target yields, deployment timelines, and pipeline descriptions involve known and unknown risks and uncertainties. Actual results may differ materially. There is no guarantee that target yields will be achieved, that principal will be returned, or that the Fund will operate as currently described.</p>
        <p style="font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;"><strong style="color:var(--white);">SECURITIES NOT REGISTERED.</strong> Interests in Draft Horse Capital Partners LLC have not been registered under the Securities Act of 1933, the Investment Company Act of 1940, or any state securities law. These interests are offered in reliance upon applicable exemptions from registration.</p>
        <p style="font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:12px;"><strong style="color:var(--white);">INVESTMENT RISK.</strong> An investment in Draft Horse Capital Partners involves a high degree of risk and is suitable only for investors who can afford to lose their entire investment and do not require liquidity during the 36-month term. Past performance of related strategies does not guarantee future results.</p>
        <p style="font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:12.5px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.8;"><strong style="color:var(--white);">NOT LEGAL OR TAX ADVICE.</strong> Nothing in this data room constitutes legal, tax, or investment advice. Prospective investors must consult their own legal, tax, and investment advisers before making any investment decision.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

      <div class="card" style="margin-top:24px;">
        <h3>Additional Regulatory &amp; Compliance Considerations</h3>

        <div class="two-col" style="gap:18px;margin-bottom:18px;">
          <div>
            <h4>Anti-Money Laundering (AML) &amp; Know-Your-Customer (KYC)</h4>
            <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;">Draft Horse Capital Partners maintains AML and KYC procedures consistent with applicable requirements for private investment funds. All prospective investors are subject to identity verification prior to subscription acceptance. The Fund requires: (i) government-issued identification for individuals; (ii) entity formation documents and beneficial ownership certification for entities; (iii) source-of-funds attestation where applicable. The Fund reserves the right to decline any subscription where AML/KYC requirements cannot be fully satisfied. SCALE LLP advises on compliance with applicable AML requirements. Institutional investors, including sovereign wealth funds, should contact the Principal to confirm the Fund's AML procedures prior to commencing subscription.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>ERISA &amp; Plan Asset Considerations</h4>
            <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;">The Fund intends to monitor its investor base to ensure that "benefit plan investors" (as defined under ERISA Section 3(42) and the U.S. Department of Labor Plan Asset Regulations at 29 C.F.R. § 2510.3-101) do not hold 25% or more of any class of the Fund's equity interests. If the 25% threshold were exceeded, the Fund's assets would be deemed "plan assets" under ERISA, subjecting the Fund's operations to ERISA's fiduciary requirements, prohibited transaction rules, and reporting obligations. The Fund does not currently intend to accept ERISA-plan capital at levels that would trigger plan asset status. Pension funds, endowments, foundations, and other benefit plan investors should consult their own ERISA counsel before subscribing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="two-col" style="gap:18px;margin-bottom:14px;">
          <div>
            <h4>FATCA &amp; Foreign Investor Considerations</h4>
            <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;">The Foreign Account Tax Compliance Act (FATCA) imposes U.S. withholding tax requirements on certain payments to foreign financial institutions and certain non-financial foreign entities that do not comply with FATCA reporting requirements. Non-U.S. investors, including sovereign wealth funds, family offices, and other foreign entities, must provide applicable FATCA documentation (including IRS Forms W-8BEN, W-8BEN-E, or W-8EXP as appropriate) prior to subscription. Sovereign wealth funds meeting the requirements of IRC Section 892 may be eligible for exemption from U.S. withholding on certain investment income — investors should confirm their IRC §892 qualification status with their own tax counsel. The Fund's tax compliance adviser (Spicer Jeffries LLP) can coordinate with prospective investors on applicable FATCA and §892 documentation requirements.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>Form D Filing Status</h4>
            <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;">The Fund is required to file Form D with the SEC within 15 days of the first sale of securities under Regulation D. SCALE LLP coordinates Form D preparation and timely filing. Additionally, certain states require notice filings (and/or filing fees) in connection with Regulation D offerings — SCALE LLP manages state "blue sky" notice filing compliance on behalf of the Fund. Prospective investors may verify Form D filing status at SEC EDGAR (www.sec.gov/cgi-bin/browse-edgar) after initial close.</p>
            <br>
            <h4>State Investment Adviser Registration</h4>
            <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;">Draft Horse Wealth Management LLC, as the Fund's managing entity, relies on applicable investment adviser exemptions under the Investment Advisers Act of 1940 and applicable state law. SCALE LLP advises on ongoing compliance with applicable adviser registration or exemption requirements as AUM grows. Investors should note that as Fund AUM increases, additional federal or state registration obligations may arise.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    <div class="section-page-notice">Draft Horse Capital Partners LLC — Confidential | For Informational Purposes Only | Not an Offer to Sell Securities</div>
  </section>

